</b></p>
<p>  <i>See</i>, <i>e.g.</i>, E/CN.4/SR.152, paras. 12-13 (&#8220;His delegation&#8217;s view [was] that the word &#8216;law&#8217;, as 
understood in the covenant, referred exclusively to laws which were not contrary to the 
principles of the [Universal] Declaration [of Human Rights].  &#8230; Unless such a formula was 
included, the text of article 5 [now 6] would be acceptable to any dictator, as there would be 
nothing to prevent him from enacting laws contrary to the spirit of the Declaration.&#8221;); 
