<p><b>95
</b>  A particularly significant example is that the recognition that mandatory death sentences were 
</p>
<p><i>per se</i> violations of human rights law stemmed from a gradual understanding through the 
adjudication of concrete cases that the &#8220;most serious crimes&#8221; limitation did not fully capture the 
concept of the non-arbitrary imposition of capital punishment.   
